  "text": "Since the detector will be located inside existing/future neutrino near detector halls, we discuss the possibility of utilizing the neutrino detectors to better enhance our sensitivity to MCP. One idea would be to place FerMINI directly in front of or behind the neutrino detector and using the liquid argon technology to provide extra information on particles traversing the MCP detector and provide a veto on SM particles that could fake an MCP signal. In addition, one can look for mixed signature combining the scintillation signature discussed in this work and the hard electron scattering signature utilizing liquid argon or Cherenkov neutrino detectors discussed in [CITATION_1] .",
